# Plan: Extract Service Layer from Route Handlers

## Context

The Express route handlers in `src/routes/products.ts` (3 handlers) and `src/routes/orders.ts` (4 handlers) mix HTTP concerns with business logic — filtering, calculations, validation, state machines, and data mutation all live inline. This refactoring extracts all business logic into dedicated service modules so route handlers only parse requests, call services, and send responses. All 15 existing integration tests (supertest-based) must continue to pass unchanged.

## Architecture After Refactoring

```
HTTP Request → Route Handler (parse req) → Service Function (pure logic) → Route Handler (format res)
```

Services have no knowledge of Express, `req`, or `res`. They accept typed arguments and return results or throw `ServiceError`.

## Files to Create

### 1. `src/services/errors.ts` — Custom error class

- `ServiceError` class extending `Error` with a `code` string property
- `ErrorCode` constants: `NOT_FOUND` (maps to 404), `VALIDATION` / `INSUFFICIENT_STOCK` / `INVALID_TRANSITION` (all map to 400)

### 2. `src/services/productService.ts` — 3 functions

| Function | Signature | Logic extracted from |
|---|---|---|
| `getProducts` | `(filters: ProductFilters) => ProductListResult` | Lines 10–44 of routes/products.ts — filtering by category/price, summary stats |
| `getProductById` | `(id: number) => ProductDetail` | Lines 49–65 — lookup, isLowStock, inventoryValue |
| `adjustProductStock` | `(id: number, adjustment: unknown) => ProductDetail` | Lines 69–97 — validate adjustment type, prevent negative stock, mutate, return computed fields |

### 3. `src/services/orderService.ts` — 4 functions

| Function | Signature | Logic extracted from |
|---|---|---|
| `getOrders` | `(filters: OrderFilters) => OrderListResult` | Lines 8–34 of routes/orders.ts — filtering, totalRevenue summary |
| `getOrderById` | `(id: number) => OrderDetail` | Lines 37–59 — lookup, enrich items with productName |
| `createOrder` | `(input: CreateOrderInput) => Order` | Lines 62–122 — validate input/items, deduct stock, calculate total, create order |
| `updateOrderStatus` | `(id: number, status: string) => Order` | Lines 125–160 — validate status value, enforce state machine transitions, mutate |

## Files to Modify

### 4. `src/types.ts` — Add new interfaces (additive only, no changes to existing types)

```typescript
export interface ProductFilters {
  category?: string;
  minPrice?: number;
  maxPrice?: number;
}

export interface ProductListResult {
  products: Product[];
  summary: { count: number; totalInventoryValue: number; averagePrice: number };
}

export interface ProductDetail extends Product {
  isLowStock: boolean;
  inventoryValue: number;
}

export interface OrderFilters {
  userId?: number;
  status?: string;
}

export interface OrderListResult {
  orders: Order[];
  summary: { count: number; totalRevenue: number };
}

export interface EnrichedOrderItem extends OrderItem {
  productName: string;
}

export interface OrderDetail extends Omit<Order, "items"> {
  items: EnrichedOrderItem[];
}
```

### 5. `src/routes/products.ts` — Refactor to thin handlers

- Remove `import { products } from "../data.js"`
- Add imports from `../services/productService.js` and `../services/errors.js`
- **GET /products**: Parse query strings into `ProductFilters` (HTTP concern — string-to-number conversion stays here), call `getProducts(filters)`, send result as JSON
- **GET /products/:id**: `parseInt` the param, call `getProductById(id)` in try/catch, map ServiceError to HTTP status
- **PATCH /products/:id/stock**: `parseInt` the param, extract `adjustment` from body, call `adjustProductStock(id, adjustment)` in try/catch

### 6. `src/routes/orders.ts` — Refactor to thin handlers

- Remove `import { orders, products, getNextOrderId } from "../data.js"`
- Add imports from `../services/orderService.js` and `../services/errors.js`
- **GET /orders**: Parse query strings into `OrderFilters`, call `getOrders(filters)`, send result
- **GET /orders/:id**: try/catch around `getOrderById(id)`
- **POST /orders**: try/catch around `createOrder(req.body)`, send 201 on success
- **PATCH /orders/:id/status**: try/catch around `updateOrderStatus(id, status)`

